From 3d71dd422225e6cb6160d9f1ad45fe6100747ac0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "Mr. Figueredo" <311303@dadeschools.net>
Date: Sun, 12 Jul 2026 03:03:48 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] Add Solver, Distractor Engine, and Prompt Renderer
 support for pyramid/cone/trapezoid/rhombus templates
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Completes the full 5-stage pipeline for the 4 new templates added in
the previous commit, closing the identified gaps in pyramid/cone
volume and surface area, and trapezoid/rhombus properties.

Solver (v1.8.0 -> v1.9.0): all four templates return a pre-computed
exact value from the generator.

Distractor Engine (v1.8.0 -> v1.9.0), each grounded in a real error,
reusing the shared buildPiCoefficientDistractors helper (built during
Chapters 11-12) for the two pi-based templates:
- pyramid_or_cone_volume: forgetting to divide by 3 (using the
  PRISM/CYLINDER volume formula instead — the single most common real
  mix-up between these related solids), forgetting to square the
  base dimension, and dividing by 2 instead of 3.
- cone_surface_area: forgetting the base circle (lateral surface area
  only), forgetting the lateral surface (base circle only), and
  confusing the height with the slant height — a genuine, very common
  mix-up specific to cones.
- trapezoid_midsegment: for the 'find midsegment' scenario, forgetting
  to divide by 2, and subtracting instead of adding; for 'find missing
  base', forgetting to double the midsegment, and forgetting to
  subtract the known base.
- rhombus_diagonal_angle: forgetting to halve at all, confusing with a
  supplementary relationship (180 - angle), and doubling instead of
  halving.

Prompt Renderer (v1.8.0 -> v1.9.0): fully-specified text-only
questions for all four templates.

Verification:
- 4 new templates x 40 seeds = 160 runs through the full 5-stage
  pipeline, 0 failures.
- Re-ran at 100 seeds x 4 templates (400 runs), 0 failures.
- Full regression: all 57 certified templates (53 previous + 4 new)
  re-verified through the complete 5-stage pipeline, 57/57 pass.
- Confirmed the Quiz Composer + Quiz Printer work end-to-end with
  these new templates included, using a concept-filtered
  ('surface_area_and_volume' + 'quadrilaterals') 8-question quiz —
  also confirmed the Composer's rejection logic correctly fires when
  requesting more questions (20) than that filtered pool actually
  contains (10 templates).

This closes the previously-identified real gaps in pyramid/cone
volume and surface area (Chapter 12) and trapezoid/rhombus properties
(Chapter 7), bringing the certified pipeline to 57 templates.
